    	<h2><a name="2003-06-28" href="#2003-06-28"><font color="#660000">2003-06-28</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105678783318479673">&nbsp;</a><br>
	An opinion piece to counter a Harvard Business Review article that took the position that IT Doesn't matter any longer, in that it is ubiquitous and conveys no more advantage.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105678783318479673">Saturday, June 28, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105678750081302756">&nbsp;</a><br>
	This is a column, apparently, and the one that I am presented with is about Learning Objects, which is apparently about education, not Objects.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105678750081302756">Saturday, June 28, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105678734836090833">&nbsp;</a><br>
	Good heavens, an article (actually a piece of criticism) by Brian Cantwell Smith in 1985.  My, my.  And I just discovered a whole series of Microsoft Press books on foo Inside Out.  I should have spotted that -- I have one of them.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105678734836090833">Saturday, June 28, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105678572214461431">&nbsp;</a><br>
	Here's an interesting MSDN article on Web Application security.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105678572214461431">Saturday, June 28, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	
    	<h2><a name="2003-06-27" href="#2003-06-27"><font color="#660000">2003-06-27</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105675853796316115">&nbsp;</a><br>
	.nbsp; This change to Blogger that has me log in all of the time when I click "Blog this" is very annoying, as is the funny number that shows up in this little note pane.  I have to erase it every time.  <br /><br />OK, why are we here.  Because the IEEE is working on some standards that include message formats for incident management.  This is tied to work on an intelligent transportation system, but incident management messages apply in lots of contexts and are related to IT events, disaster recovery, and other important areas.  A place to come back to once I can get the IEEE web site to behave.<br /><br />And don't you hate it when you get linked to a PDF file without the option of deciding whether you want to go through that (especially if you don't have the plug-in or it is not working!) or not.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105675853796316115">Friday, June 27, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	
    	<h2><a name="2003-06-26" href="#2003-06-26"><font color="#660000">2003-06-26</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105665633082706860">&nbsp;</a><br>
	.&nbsp; This article is about cyberjacking and the increasing criminality of hacking and spamming activity.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105665633082706860">Thursday, June 26, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105665620331340857">&nbsp;</a><br>
	.&nbsp; An article on work being done to experiment using an expanding Internet shadow universe.&nbsp; This may be a place for collaborative work and also distributed Miser operation.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105665620331340857">Thursday, June 26, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="105665587021557415">&nbsp;</a><br>
	.&nbsp; Here's a nice article on how to prepare for a dissertation and manage it through to completion.   A funny kind of article, in one sense, but has some nice tidbits.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#105665587021557415">Thursday, June 26, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	
    	<h2><a name="2003-06-23" href="#2003-06-23"><font color="#660000">2003-06-23</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952675">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.codeproject.com/java/javacom.asp">The Code Project - Embed ActiveX controls inside Java GUI - Java Programming</a>.&nbsp; Something very interesting to dig into as we get going here on the ins and outs of Java.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952675">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952380">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.mestevens.com/site/doc/mestevens-102.htm">Java Foundations Tutorial</a>.&nbsp; A PowerPoint slide show.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952380">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952336">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.pricegrabber.com/search_fullinfobk.php/isbn=0201781298/ut=3fe46499fe0a0a27">Java Software Solutions - PriceGrabber.com - Comparison Shopping Beyond Compare</a>.&nbsp; This is the weird way I found out about Java Software Solutions: Foundations of Program Design (updated July 2002 edition).<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952336">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952224">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.rahder.com/LayoutPrinter/PageTraining.html">Finding order in complexity: Max Rahder</a>.&nbsp; Here's a familiar-looking curriculum with a Primer and a Foundations course.  The motivation is one I subscribe to.  I wonder who is the author of what?<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952224">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952125">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://info.baeumle.com/java/intro/">Introduction to Java - Peter Baeumle-Courth</a>.&nbsp; Here's an introduction for C++ programmers that touches on foundational issues for Java.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952125">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95952077">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.onsitejava.com/outlines.html">Onsite Java: Java training at your site.</a>.&nbsp; There is a Java Primer and a Java Foundations course.   The PDF outline of the Foundations course is interesting.  It might even fit what I am looking for as an introduction for developers and advanced students.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95952077">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95951198">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.idg.net/go.cgi?id=260451">IDG.net</a>.&nbsp; Well, the IDG guys have aggregated and framed the Weintraub article.  OK, let's see what happens if I search for my second-choice title.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95951198">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95951147">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.briansbooks.com/catalog/books/007882477X">Java Beans Programming from the Ground Up (Ground Up Series) by O'Neil, Joseph (Osborne McGraw-Hill)</a>.&nbsp; OK, a whole Ground Up Series.  Tsk, tsk.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95951147">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95951103">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.itdart.com/tutorial1.asp?tutorial=Learn Java from the ground up">Learn Java from the Ground Up || ITdart Tutorials || ITdart::IT Training Guide</a>.&nbsp; This is part of a training guide tutorial without pictures.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95951103">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95951015">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.robsell.com/books/jnut/ch02_01.htm">Java Syntax from the Ground Up (Java in a Nutshell)</a>.&nbsp; Oh, and a chapter in the on-line version of Java in a Nutshell.  My goodness.  Well, it is nice to know that book is on-line and can also be reviewed for ground-up ideas.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95951015">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95950888">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.javajunkies.org/index.pl?lastnode_id=1138&node_id=1107">javajunkies.org (1107) Learning Java from the ground up</a>.&nbsp; And yet another use of the phrase.&nbsp; OK, I get it, the title doesn't work for my next book!  I have another idea, but meanwhile, I want to capture all of these nice threads on getting started.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95950888">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95950805">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.geocities.com/lkp550/JAVAHUT.htm">Learn Java from the ground up</a>.&nbsp; Another approach on JAVAHUT.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95950805">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95950754">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.bellaonline.com/articles/art3201.asp">Learn Java From The Ground Up : Part I - Java at BellaOnline</a>.&nbsp; Another site, this one appearing to republish the Jacob Weintraub series that I just found on JavaWorld.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95950754">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95950659">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.javaworld.com/javaworld/jw-03-2000/jw-0331-java101.html">Learn Java from the ground up</a>.&nbsp; Oops, I was thinking that Java From the Ground Up would be a great title for introducing people to Java from a foundation perspective.  Maybe I can't use that.  On the other hand, this Java 101 material from a March 2000 JavaWorld series is useful to compare and explore and refer people to who are having trouble getting started.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95950659">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="95948485">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.acm.org/ubiquity/interviews/b_kotelly_2.html">ACM: Ubiquity - A Designing Life: Blade Kotelly</a>.&nbsp; This is just wonderful.&nbsp; Simply wonderful.&nbsp; Why is Computer Programming 4 Everyone (CP4E) for Everyone?  Because we are all designers, every one.&nbsp; This goes into my must-read notice to all my classmates in the M.Sc in IT OOP through Java course.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#95948485">Monday, June 23, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>


